# 🏗️ Full-Stack Project Management Application — Complete System Architecture

> **Source**: Synthesized from 5.5-hour GreatStack tutorial (104 transcript chunks, 2550 lines).
> **Scope**: Production-ready HLD, LLD, Schema, APIs, RBAC, Folder Structure & Roadmap.

---

## 1. High-Level Architecture (HLD)

### 1.1 System Context Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Clients"
        WebApp["React SPA (Vite + Tailwind)"]
        FutureMobile["Future: Mobile App"]
    end

    subgraph "Identity & Access Management"
        Clerk["Clerk Auth Platform"]
        ClerkOrg["Clerk Organizations"]
    end

    subgraph "Application Layer"
        Express["Node.js / Express API Server"]
        Inngest["Inngest Worker (Background Jobs)"]
    end

    subgraph "Data Layer"
        NeonDB["Neon Serverless PostgreSQL"]
        Prisma["Prisma ORM"]
    end

    subgraph "Notification Layer"
        SMTP["SMTP Provider (Brevo/SendinBlue)"]
        NodeMailer["NodeMailer Transport"]
    end

    subgraph "Hosting & CI/CD"
        Vercel["Vercel Platform"]
        GitHub["GitHub Repository"]
    end

    WebApp -->|HTTPS/REST + JWT Bearer| Express
    WebApp -->|Auth UI Components| Clerk
    Clerk -->|Webhooks: user/org events| Inngest
    Inngest -->|Event-driven job execution| Express
    Express -->|Prisma Client| NeonDB
    Inngest -->|Prisma Client| NeonDB
    Inngest -->|Send emails via| NodeMailer
    NodeMailer -->|SMTP| SMTP
    GitHub -->|Git push triggers| Vercel
    Vercel -->|Hosts| Express
    Vercel -->|Hosts| WebApp
```

### 1.2 Tier Breakdown

| Tier | Technology | Purpose |
|:-----|:-----------|:--------|
| **Presentation** | React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Redux Toolkit | SPA with state management, theming (light/dark), routing |
| **API Gateway** | Express.js (Node.js) | REST API, Clerk middleware, route protection |
| **Background Jobs** | Inngest | Webhook processing, scheduled email reminders, event-driven flows |
| **ORM** | Prisma | Type-safe DB access, migrations, schema-first design |
| **Database** | Neon PostgreSQL (Serverless) | Relational data storage with auto-scaling |
| **Auth** | Clerk | User auth (Google, Email), organization management, role assignment |
| **Email** | NodeMailer + Brevo SMTP | Task assignment emails, due-date reminder emails |
| **Hosting** | Vercel (Frontend + Backend) | Git-to-live CI/CD, preview deployments, edge functions |

### 1.3 Data Flow — Task Assignment Lifecycle

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Admin/Team Lead
    participant Frontend as React App
    participant API as Express API
    participant DB as Neon PostgreSQL
    participant Inngest as Inngest Worker
    participant SMTP as Email (Brevo)
    participant Assignee as Assigned User

    Admin->>Frontend: Fill task form + click Create
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/tasks {title, assigneeId, dueDate...}
    API->>DB: prisma.task.create({data})
    API->>Inngest: inngest.send("app/task.assigned", {taskId, origin})
    API-->>Frontend: 200 {task, message}
    
    Inngest->>DB: prisma.task.findUnique(taskId)
    Inngest->>SMTP: sendEmail({to: assignee, subject, body})
    SMTP-->>Assignee: "New Task Assignment" email
    
    Note over Inngest: step.sleepUntil(dueDate)
    
    Inngest->>DB: Check task.status !== "DONE"
    alt Task still pending
        Inngest->>SMTP: sendEmail({to: assignee, subject: "Reminder"})
        SMTP-->>Assignee: "Task Reminder" email
    end
```

