### 2.3 State Management (Redux Toolkit)

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "workspaceSlice.js"
        WS_State["State: {workspaces[], currentWorkspace, loading}"]
        WS_Reducers["Reducers: setWorkspaces, setCurrentWorkspace, addWorkspace, updateWorkspace, deleteWorkspace, addProject, addTask, updateTask, deleteTask"]
        WS_Thunks["Async Thunk: fetchWorkspaces"]
        WS_Extra["extraReducers: pending/fulfilled/rejected"]
    end
```

**Key State Operations**:
- `fetchWorkspaces` — calls `GET /api/workspaces` with Bearer token, populates entire workspace tree
- `setCurrentWorkspace` — persists workspace ID to `localStorage` for session continuity
- `addProject/addTask` — optimistically updates state after successful API calls

