## 5. RBAC System (Roles + Permissions)

### 5.1 Role Hierarchy

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Workspace Level"
        WA["ADMIN"] -->|can do everything| WM["MEMBER"]
    end
    
    subgraph "Project Level"
        TL["Team Lead (project.teamLead)"] -->|can manage project| PM["Project Member"]
    end
```

### 5.2 Permissions Matrix

| Action | Workspace ADMIN | Workspace MEMBER | Project Team Lead | Project Member |
|:-------|:-:|:-:|:-:|:-:|
| **Workspace** | | | | |
| Create workspace | ✅ (via Clerk) | ✅ (via Clerk) | — | — |
| Update workspace | ✅ (via Clerk) | ❌ | — | — |
| Delete workspace | ✅ (via Clerk) | ❌ | — | — |
| Invite members | ✅ | ❌ | — | — |
| Add members (API) | ✅ | ❌ | — | — |
| View workspace data | ✅ | ✅ | — | — |
| **Projects** | | | | |
| Create project | ✅ | ❌ | — | — |
| Update project | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Add project member | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| View project | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Tasks** | | | | |
| Create task | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Update task status | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Delete task | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| View tasks | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| **Comments** | | | | |
| Add comment | — | — | ✅ | ✅ |
| View comments | — | — | ✅ | ✅ |

### 5.3 Authorization Implementation

**Middleware Layer** (`authMiddleware.js`):
```
protect() → extracts userId via req.auth() → returns 401 if missing → calls next()
```

**Controller-Level Checks** (in each controller function):
1. **Workspace admin check**: `workspace.members.some(m => m.userId === userId && m.role === "ADMIN")`
2. **Project lead check**: `project.teamLead === userId`
3. **Project membership check**: `project.members.find(m => m.userId === userId)`
4. **Assignee validation**: `project.members.find(m => m.user.id === assigneeId)`

### 5.4 Production Enhancements (Inferred)

> [!TIP]
> The tutorial implements basic RBAC. For production, consider these additions:

- **OWNER role**: Separate from ADMIN for workspace creators (prevent self-demotion)
- **VIEWER role**: Read-only access for stakeholders
- **Permission-based model**: Replace role checks with granular permissions (`project:create`, `task:assign`, etc.)
- **CASL/AccessControl library**: Centralize authorization logic instead of scattering checks in controllers
- **Audit logging**: Track who performed what action and when

