```

### 6.3 Backend (`server/`)

```
server/
├── config/
│   ├── prisma.js              # Prisma client init (PrismaNeon adapter + WebSocket)
│   └── nodeMailer.js          # SMTP transporter + sendEmail function
├── controllers/
│   ├── workspaceController.js # getUserWorkspaces, addMember
│   ├── projectController.js   # createProject, updateProject, addMember
│   ├── taskController.js      # createTask, updateTask, deleteTask
│   └── commentController.js   # addComment, getTaskComments
├── inngest/
│   └── index.js               # Inngest client + 8 event functions + functions array
├── middlewares/
│   └── authMiddleware.js      # protect() — validates Clerk JWT
├── prisma/
│   └── schema.prisma          # Full database schema
├── routes/
│   ├── workspaceRoutes.js     # GET /, POST /add-member
│   ├── projectRoutes.js       # POST /, PUT /, POST /:id/add-member
│   ├── taskRoutes.js          # POST /, PUT /:id, POST /delete
│   └── commentRoutes.js       # POST /, GET /:taskId
├── .env                       # All server env vars (see below)
├── server.js                  # Express app entry point
├── package.json               # type: "module", scripts
└── vercel.json                # Express serverless config
```

### 6.4 Environment Variables

**Backend `.env`**:
```env
NODE_ENV=development
CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...?sslmode=require
DIRECT_URL=postgresql://...?sslmode=require
INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=...
INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=signkey-...
SENDER_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com
SMTP_USER=...
SMTP_PASS=...
```

**Frontend `.env`**:
```env
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
VITE_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000
```

---

## 7. Step-by-Step Development Roadmap

### Phase 1: Foundation & Infrastructure (Week 1)

| # | Task | Details |
|:-:|:-----|:--------|
| 1 | **Initialize monorepo** | Create `project-management/` with `client/` and `server/` directories |
| 2 | **Scaffold frontend** | Fork/clone GreatStack template OR `npx create-vite@latest ./` with React + Tailwind |
| 3 | **Install frontend deps** | `@clerk/clerk-react`, `@reduxjs/toolkit`, `react-redux`, `react-router-dom`, `axios`, `recharts`, `lucide-react`, `react-hot-toast`, `date-fns` |
| 4 | **Scaffold backend** | `npm init -y`, install `express`, `cors`, `dotenv`, `nodemon` (dev), set `"type": "module"` |
| 5 | **Create basic Express server** | `server.js` with JSON parsing, CORS, health route, `app.listen(5000)` |
| 6 | **Setup Neon PostgreSQL** | Create project on [neon.tech](https://neon.tech), get connection strings |
| 7 | **Configure Prisma** | Install `prisma`, `@prisma/client`, `@prisma/adapter-neon`, `ws`. Create `schema.prisma`, run `npx prisma db push` |
| 8 | **Setup Clerk** | Create app on [clerk.com](https://clerk.com), enable Google + Email sign-in. Install `@clerk/clerk-react` (client) + `@clerk/express` (server) |
| 9 | **Integrate Clerk in frontend** | Add `ClerkProvider` in `main.jsx`, add auth guards in `Layout.jsx` |
| 10 | **Add Clerk middleware to backend** | `app.use(clerkMiddleware())`, create `protect` middleware |

### Phase 2: User & Workspace Management (Week 2)

| # | Task | Details |
|:-:|:-----|:--------|
| 11 | **Setup Inngest** | Create account, install `inngest`, create `inngest/index.js` with client |
| 12 | **Configure Clerk → Inngest webhooks** | Connect Clerk webhooks to Inngest endpoint |
| 13 | **Implement user sync functions** | `syncUserCreation`, `syncUserDeletion`, `syncUserUpdation` (3 Inngest functions) |
| 14 | **Enable Clerk Organizations** | Dashboard → Configure → Organization Management → Enable |
| 15 | **Implement workspace sync functions** | `syncWorkspaceCreation` (+ add creator as ADMIN), `syncWorkspaceUpdation`, `syncWorkspaceDeletion`, `syncWorkspaceMemberCreation` (4 functions) |
| 16 | **Build workspace API** | `workspaceController.js` + `workspaceRoutes.js`: get workspaces, add member |
| 17 | **Build workspace frontend** | `WorkspaceDropdown.jsx` with Clerk `useOrganizationList`, `CreateOrganization` component, `fetchWorkspaces` thunk |
| 18 | **Deploy backend to Vercel** | Push to GitHub, deploy `server/` on Vercel, sync Inngest app |
| 19 | **Test workspace flow** | Create org → verify DB entry → switch orgs → invite member → verify invitation email |

### Phase 3: Project Management (Week 3)

| # | Task | Details |
|:-:|:-----|:--------|
| 20 | **Build project API** | `projectController.js`: createProject (admin check, team lead lookup, member assignment), updateProject (admin OR lead), addMember (lead only) |
| 21 | **Add project routes** | `POST /`, `PUT /`, `POST /:id/add-member` |
| 22 | **Build project frontend** | `CreateProjectDialog.jsx` form → API → Redux, `ProjectSettings.jsx` update form, `AddProjectMember.jsx` |
| 23 | **Build dashboard** | `StatsGrid.jsx` (total projects, active, completed, my tasks, overdue), `TaskSummary.jsx`, project overview cards |
| 24 | **Test project flow** | Create project → verify in DB → update settings → add member → verify permissions |

### Phase 4: Task System & Email Notifications (Week 4)

| # | Task | Details |
|:-:|:-----|:--------|
| 25 | **Build task API** | `taskController.js`: createTask (lead check, assignee validation), updateTask (lead check), deleteTask (bulk, lead check) |
| 26 | **Add task routes** | `POST /`, `PUT /:id`, `POST /delete` |
| 27 | **Configure NodeMailer** | Install `nodemailer`, create `nodeMailer.js` with Brevo SMTP transporter |
| 28 | **Implement email Inngest function** | `sendTaskAssignmentEmail`: send on creation + `step.sleepUntil(dueDate)` + send reminder if not DONE |
| 29 | **Build task frontend** | `CreateTaskDialog.jsx` form, `ProjectTask.jsx` (list, status dropdown, bulk delete), task detail page |
| 30 | **Test task flow** | Create task → verify email sent → change status → delete → verify reminder scheduling |

### Phase 5: Comments, Analytics & Polish (Week 5)

| # | Task | Details |
|:-:|:-----|:--------|
| 31 | **Build comment API** | `commentController.js`: addComment (member check), getTaskComments |
| 32 | **Add comment routes** | `POST /`, `GET /:taskId` |
| 33 | **Comment frontend** | `TaskDetails.jsx` comment list + input field + post button |
| 34 | **Analytics page** | `ProjectAnalytics.jsx` with Recharts: task by status (pie), task by type (bar), task by priority (bar) |
| 35 | **Calendar view** | `ProjectCalendar.jsx` showing tasks by due date |
| 36 | **Theme system** | Light/dark mode toggle, persist preference in `localStorage` |
| 37 | **Sidebar navigation** | Expandable project list, my tasks list, settings opens Clerk UserProfile |
| 38 | **Search** functionality | Filter projects and tasks in lists |

### Phase 6: Testing, Deployment & Hardening (Week 6)

| # | Task | Details |
|:-:|:-----|:--------|
| 39 | **Backend tests** | Jest: test Clerk webhook sync, test RBAC on each endpoint, test email sending |
| 40 | **Frontend tests** | Cypress E2E: signup → create org → create project → add task → verify email → comment |
| 41 | **Deploy frontend to Vercel** | Root directory: `client/`, set `VITE_BASE_URL` to backend URL |
| 42 | **Configure Clerk redirect URLs** | Set fallback development host + production domain |
| 43 | **Update environment variables** | Change `NODE_ENV=production`, update all URLs |
| 44 | **Security hardening** | Rate limiting, input validation (Zod/Joi), SQL injection prevention (Prisma handles), XSS protection, CORS whitelist |
| 45 | **Monitoring** | Add Sentry (frontend + backend), structured logging (Pino), Vercel Analytics |
| 46 | **Performance** | Add Redis caching for frequent queries, pagination on task/comment lists, lazy loading |

---

## Production Enhancements (Beyond Tutorial)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The tutorial covers a complete MVP. For production readiness, add these:

| Category | Enhancement |
|:---------|:------------|
| **Security** | Rate limiting (`express-rate-limit`), input validation (Zod), helmet.js, CORS whitelist |
| **Performance** | Redis caching (dashboard metrics), DB query optimization (indexes), pagination, infinite scroll |
| **Real-time** | WebSocket (Socket.io) for live task updates, comment notifications, presence indicators |
| **File handling** | Attachment uploads on tasks/comments via S3/Cloudinary |
| **Search** | Full-text search with PostgreSQL `tsvector` or Elasticsearch |
| **Notifications** | In-app notification center, push notifications (FCM), Slack/Discord integrations |
| **Activity feed** | Audit log with `ActivityLog` model tracking all user actions |
| **Billing** | Stripe integration for premium workspace features (more members, storage) |
| **Testing** | Unit tests (Jest), integration tests (Supertest), E2E (Cypress/Playwright) |
| **CI/CD** | GitHub Actions for lint, test, deploy pipeline with staging environment |
| **Mobile** | React Native or Flutter client consuming the same REST API |
